        "### Stationarity Testing & Train/Test Split\n",
        "We use the Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) test to check if each series is stationary.\n",
        "A p-value ≤ 0.05 means the series is stationary. Non-stationary series will be\n",
        "differenced (d=1) before feeding into ARIMA."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dMgO5R_L7X2H"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller\n",
        "\n",
        "def adf_test(series, name):\n",
        "    result = adfuller(series.dropna())\n",
        "    p = result[1]\n",
        "    stat = result[0]\n",
        "    conclusion = \"✅ STATIONARY\" if p <= 0.05 else \"⚠️ NON-STATIONARY (needs differencing)\"\n",
        "    print(f\"  {name:<25} | ADF: {stat:7.3f} | p-value: {p:.4f} | {conclusion}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"=== Augmented Dickey-Fuller Stationarity Tests ===\\n\")\n",
        "adf_test(df['Inflation'],   'Inflation')\n",
        "adf_test(df['USDZMW'],      'USDZMW')\n",
        "adf_test(df['Copper_USD'],  'Copper_USD')\n",
        "\n",
        "df_diff = df.diff().dropna()\n",
        "print(\"\\n=== After First-Order Differencing ===\\n\")\n",
        "adf_test(df_diff['Inflation'],   'Inflation (d=1)')\n",
        "adf_test(df_diff['USDZMW'],      'USDZMW (d=1)')\n",
        "adf_test(df_diff['Copper_USD'],  'Copper_USD (d=1)')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train / Test Split\n",
        "train = df.iloc[:-5]\n",
        "test  = df.iloc[-5:]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n📦 Training window : {train.index.min().year} – {train.index.max().year} ({len(train)} years)\")\n",
        "print(f\"📦 Testing  window : {test.index.min().year}  – {test.index.max().year}  ({len(test)} years)\")"
      ],
